From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000011 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ESP32-S3 Web Simulator contributors <noreply@example.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 21:15:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 11/11] build: honor explicitly disabled slirp

The disabled feature state is not auto, so the old condition entered the
dependency block and wrapped a disabled dependency in a declare_dependency.
Keep SLiRP absent when the operator explicitly compiles it out.

---
 meson.build | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/meson.build b/meson.build
--- a/meson.build
+++ b/meson.build
@@ -1216,7 +1216,7 @@ else
 endif
 
 slirp = not_found
-if not get_option('slirp').auto() or have_system
+if get_option('slirp').enabled() or (get_option('slirp').auto() and have_system)
   slirp_dep = dependency('slirp', required: get_option('slirp'),
                      method: 'pkg-config',
                      static: true)
